"Flush the Fat Away" Vegetable Soup

1 medium sweet potato, peeled and cut into 1" cubes
3 carrots, peeled and sliced
1 salk celery, diced
1 small yellow onion, diced
1 clove garlic, minced
pinch of kosher salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
1/8 tsp allspices
1 tsp paprika
1 bay leaf
2x15oz cans navy beans, drained and rinsed (can use black beans)
4 c vegetable broth (low sodium)
1 14.5oz can diced tomatoes (optional)
4 c baby spinach, loosely packed
1 tbsp plus 1 tsp evoo (optional, for serving)


Add all ingredients, except spinach and olive oil, to slow cooker. Cover and cook on low 6-8 hrs, or until the vegetables are tender. Add spinach, stir and continue cooking just until wilted, ~5min. 

To cook on stovetop: cook for 2hrs, stirring every 15 min, add spiach at the end and cook until wilted.

1 serving = 1 1/4 c (can use for 3 day detox)
